{sup|{{note|b|[b]}}}} signifies an additional producer\n* The deluxe edition of the album was initially released on March 23, featuring tracks 2\u20136 of the ''Remixes'' EP as bonus tracks. On March 30, the release was updated to include three new bonus tracks before the remixes. On April 3, the remixes were released as a separate [[extended play|EP]], with track 1 added, while the deluxe edition of the album was amended to end at \"Final Lullaby\".<ref name=\"EP\">{{cite tweet|number=1244747961138987008|title=just a heads up, deluxe will end with final lullaby. putting remixes on a separate ep. it'll be updated friday. xo|user=theweeknd|author=The Weeknd|authorlink=The Weeknd|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n\n'''Sample credits'''\n* \"Scared to Live\" contains interpolations from \"[[Your Song]]\", written by [[Elton John]] and [[Bernie Taupin|Bernard Taupin]].\n\n==Personnel==\nCredits adapted from liner notes.<ref name=\"LN\"/>\n\n'''Musicians'''\n* [[Metro Boomin]] \u2013 keyboards {{small|(track 7)}}, programming {{small|(track 7)}}\n* [[The Weeknd]] \u2013 vocals, keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 1, 2, 3, 7, 9, 13)}}, bass, guitar, drums {{small|(track 9)}}\n* [[Max Martin]] \u2013 bass, drums, guitar, keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 3, 9)}}\n* [[Oscar Holter]] \u2013 bass, drums, guitar, keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 3, 9)}}\n* [[Illangelo]] \u2013 keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 1, 2, 13)}}\n* [[Jason Quenneville|DaHeala]] \u2013 keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 1, 2, 13)}}\n* [[Frank Dukes]] \u2013 keyboards, programming {{small|(tracks 1, 13)}}\n* Ricky Reed \u2013 keyboards, programming {{small|(track 2)}}\n* Nate Mercereau \u2013 keyboards, programming {{small|(track 2)}}\n\n'''Technical'''\n* Illangelo \u2013 engineering, mixing {{small|(tracks 1, 2, 7, 13)}}\n* Shin Kamiyama \u2013 engineering {{small|(tracks 1, 2, 3, 7, 9, 13)}}\n* Ethan Shumaker \u2013 engineering {{small|(track 2)}}\n* Matt Cohn \u2013 mixing {{small|(tracks 12, 14)}}\n* Serban Ghenea \u2013 mixing {{small|(tracks 3, 4, 9, 10, 11)}}\n* John Hanes \u2013 engineering for mixing {{small|(tracks 3, 4, 9, 10, 11)}}\n* Cory Bice \u2013 engineering assistant {{small|(tracks 3, 4, 9, 10, 11)}}\n* Jeremy Lertola \u2013 engineering assistant {{small|(tracks 3, 4, 9, 10, 11)}}\n* Sean Klein \u2013 engineering assistant {{small|(track 9)}}\n* Dave Kutch \u2013 mastering {{small|(tracks 1\u201314)}}\n* Kevin Peterson \u2013 mastering {{small|(tracks 1\u201314)}}\n\n==Charts==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\"| Chart (2020)\n! scope=\"col\"| Peak<br />position\n|-\n{{album chart|Australia|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Austria|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Flanders|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Wallonia|2|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardCanada|1|artist=The Weeknd|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Czech|1|date=202013|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Denmark|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Netherlands|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Estonian Albums (''[[Eesti Ekspress]]'')<ref name=\":4\">{{cite web|url=https://ekspress.delfi.ee/areen/eesti-tipp-40-muusikas-selle-nadala-kangelased-on-the-weeknd-ja-ag?id=89401195|title=ALBUMID TIPP-40|work=[[Eesti Ekspress]]|date=March 31, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{album chart|Finland|2|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| French Albums ([[Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|SNEP]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://snepmusique.com/les-tops/le-top-de-la-semaine/top-albums/?semaine=13?&annee=2020&categorie=Top%20Albums|title=Top Albums (Week 13, 2020)|publisher=Syndicat National de l'\u00c9dition Phonographique|language=French|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n| 2\n|-\n{{album chart|Germany4|5|id=401628|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Hungary|17|year=2020|week=13|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 2, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Ireland3|1|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Italy|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Japan Hot Albums (''[[Billboard Japan]]'')<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard-japan.com/charts/detail?a=hot_albums&year=2020&month=03&day=30|title=Billboard Japan Hot Albums 2020/3/30|work=[[Billboard Japan]]|language=Japanese|accessdate=March 27, 2020}}</ref>\n| 76\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Lithuanian Albums ([[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]])<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.agata.lt/lt/naujienos/savaites-klausomiausi-2020w13/|title=2020 13-os savait\u0117s klausomiausi (TOP 100)|language=Lithuanian|publisher=[[AGATA (organization)|AGATA]]|accessdate=March 29, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{album chart|New Zealand|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Norway|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Scotland|2|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| Spanish Albums ([[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a|PROMUSICAE]])<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.promusicae.es/listas/semana/4348-%C3%81lbumes-semana-13-2020|title=Top 100 Albumes \u2013 Semana 13: del 20.3.2020 al 26.3.2020|publisher=[[Productores de M\u00fasica de Espa\u00f1a]]|language=Spanish|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}</ref>\n| 3\n|-\n{{album chart|Sweden|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Switzerland|1|artist=The Weeknd|album=After Hours|rowheader=true|accessdate=April 1, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|UK2|1|date=20200327|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 28, 2020}}\n|-\n{{album chart|Billboard200|1|artist=The Weeknd|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| US [[Rolling Stone Top 200|''Rolling Stone'' Top 200]]<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rollingstone.com/charts/albums/2020-04-02/|title=Top 200 Albums|work=[[Rolling Stone]]|date=April 2, 2020|accessdate=April 8, 2020}}</ref>\n| 1\n|-\n{{album chart|BillboardRandBHipHop|1|artist=The Weeknd|rowheader=true|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}\n|}\n\n==Release history==\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\"\n! scope=\"col\"| Region\n! scope=\"col\"| Date\n! scope=\"col\"| Format\n! scope=\"col\"| Version\n! scope=\"col\"| Label\n! scope=\"col\"| References\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" rowspan=\"7\"| Various\n| March 20, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[Compact disc|CD]]|[[Music download|digital download]]|[[Streaming media|streaming]]}}\n| Standard\n| rowspan=\"7\"| {{hlist|[[XO (record label)|XO]]|[[Republic Records|Republic]]}}\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.mtv.com/news/3160604/the-weeknd-after-hours-stream-album/|title=The Weeknd's 'Brain-Melting' New Album After Hours Is Finally Here|website=MTV News|last=Roth|first=Madeline|date=March 20, 2020|accessdate=March 31, 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n| March 23, 2020\n| rowspan=\"3\"| {{hlist|Digital download|streaming}}\n| Original deluxe\n|<ref name=\"Hypebeast1\"/>\n|-\n| March 30, 2020\n| Updated deluxe\n|<ref name=\"Pitchfork1\"/>\n|-\n| April 3, 2020\n| Remix EP\n|<ref name=\"EP\"/>\n|-\n| June 5, 2020\n| {{hlist|[[LP record|LP]]}}\n| Standard\n|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://thesoundofvinyl.com/*/*/After-Hours-Double-LP/6E690000000|title=The Sound of Vinyl|website=The Sound of Vinyl|accessdate=March 31, 20